{{!< default}}
{{!-- custom-about: About page for Mere Orthodoxy. Routed to /about/
     via routes.yaml; also duplicated as page-about.hbs so Ghost's
     auto-template picks it up over any existing Ghost About page.
     Matches the editorial feel used on index.hbs and
     custom-membership.hbs: dark hero, highlighted key phrase,
     pilcrow flourishes between sections, dropcap opener, Roman
     numeral list, circular team portraits. Team and editorial board
     are hardcoded here; swap names in this file when they change. --}}

<main class="about">

  <section class="hero about-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="about-hero-grid">
        <div class="about-hero-content">
          <p class="hero-kicker"><span class="dot"></span> About Mere&nbsp;Orthodoxy</p>
          <h1 class="hero-headline about-hero-headline">
            Forming Christians in the Church to participate in culture <span class="highlight about-hero-highlight"><em>for&nbsp;the&nbsp;common&nbsp;good</em></span>.
          </h1>
          <p class="hero-sub">A reader-supported publication recovering the best of the Christian tradition and applying it to the issues of our time.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="about-hero-image" aria-hidden="true">
          <img src="{{asset "images/about-hero.jpg"}}" alt="" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="about-body">
    <div class="container container-narrow">

      <div class="about-prose">
        <p class="about-lede hero-excerpt-dropcap">Blaise Pascal once wrote that the Christian faith is &ldquo;Worthy of reverence because it really understands human nature. Attractive because it promises true good.&rdquo; We believe individuals, families, churches, communities, and nations are renewed when they remember this truth. In a world that seeks to dominate or desert the culture, we seek to renew it.</p>
        <p>We do this through recovering the best of the Christian tradition throughout the ages and applying it to the issues of our time. Our aim is to use media to strengthen faith, virtue, and knowledge for the flourishing of our common bonds and to be faithful to the call of Christ on all of life.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="flourish">{{> "flourish-mark"}}</div>

      <div class="section-intro">
        <p class="eyebrow">The Namesake</p>
        <h2 class="section-heading"><em>Mere, and orthodox.</em></h2>
      </div>
      <div class="about-prose">
        <p>Mere Orthodoxy gets its name from combining the two great works of C.S. Lewis and G.K. Chesterton, <em>Mere Christianity</em> and <em>Orthodoxy</em>. These books and authors represent some of the best of the Christian tradition. Lewis, a Protestant, and Chesterton, a Catholic, both understood that there is an irreducible core of the Christian faith that unites all Christians across denomination and tradition. They knew that the core of the Christian faith was reasonable, defensible, and beautiful, and when that truth is clearly and carefully articulated, it makes sense of everything else. As Chesterton wrote, &ldquo;Instinct after instinct was answered by doctrine after doctrine.&rdquo; We believe that Christianity is the key to the world.</p>
        <p>This core is what we guard and are guided by. Most succinctly expressed in the Nicene Creed, we want to answer the instincts of individuals and the broader culture with &ldquo;doctrine after doctrine.&rdquo; Not merely as a defense of the truth&mdash;though we will certainly defend it&mdash;or as an intellectual exercise&mdash;though it is fascinating&mdash;but as the key that unlocks the mystery and wonder of God and his creation.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="flourish">{{> "flourish-mark"}}</div>

      <div class="section-intro">
        <p class="eyebrow">The Method</p>
        <h2 class="section-heading"><em>Words that bring life.</em></h2>
      </div>
      <div class="about-prose">
        <p>We believe that words have the power of life and death. This is why we are committed to using words, amplified through writing, audio, and video, to spread ideas that bring life. We believe in renewing the Church with a Protestant Catholicity, a faith that is deeply rooted in the distinctives of the Protestant Reformation but sees itself situated in the one, holy, catholic, and apostolic church and receives all of the Church&rsquo;s treasures. We believe in renewing the culture with a Solidarity Conservatism, which seeks to preserve the thought that has led to the flourishing of Western civilization while seeing ourselves in membership with one another as image bearers of God.</p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="about-vision">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-intro">
        <p class="eyebrow">The Vision</p>
        <h2 class="section-heading"><em>We want to see&hellip;</em></h2>
      </div>

      <ol class="about-vision-grid">
        <li class="about-vision-item">
          <span class="about-vision-numeral">I</span>
          <h3 class="about-vision-label"><em>Individuals</em></h3>
          <p class="about-vision-body">Formed in faith, virtue, and reason.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="about-vision-item">
          <span class="about-vision-numeral">II</span>
          <h3 class="about-vision-label"><em>Churches</em></h3>
          <p class="about-vision-body">Formed in scripture, sacrament, and conviction.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="about-vision-item">
          <span class="about-vision-numeral">III</span>
          <h3 class="about-vision-label"><em>Communities</em></h3>
          <p class="about-vision-body">Formed in membership, solidarity, and tradition.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="about-vision-item">
          <span class="about-vision-numeral">IV</span>
          <h3 class="about-vision-label"><em>Public leaders</em></h3>
          <p class="about-vision-body">Formed in character, limits, and locality.</p>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <p class="about-vision-coda">
        This is why we write and speak about church, culture, formation, family, theology, technology, and more. Through faithfulness to Christ in every square inch of life, we seek the renewal of the Church and culture in our lifetime.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="about-team">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-intro">
        <p class="eyebrow">The Team</p>
        <h2 class="section-heading"><em>Who we are.</em></h2>
      </div>

      {{!-- Team cards — photos pulled from each person's Ghost
           author-* tag feature_image via {{#get}}. Role, name, and
           bio stay hardcoded because roles live here on the About
           page, not in tag metadata. If a tag slug doesn't match,
           the {{else}} branch falls back to name initials. --}}
      <div class="contributors-grid about-team-grid">
        <div class="contributor-card contributor-card--static">
          <div class="contributor-card-portrait" aria-hidden="true">
            {{#get "tags" filter="slug:author-jake-meador" limit="1"}}
              {{#foreach tags}}{{#if feature_image}}<img src="{{img_url feature_image size="s"}}" alt="Jake Meador" />{{else}}<span class="contributor-card-initial">Jake Meador</span>{{/if}}{{/foreach}}
            {{else}}<span class="contributor-card-initial">Jake Meador</span>{{/get}}
          </div>
          <div class="contributor-card-body">
            <h3 class="contributor-card-name"><em>Jake Meador</em></h3>
            <p class="contributor-card-role">Editor-in-Chief &amp; Chairman</p>
            <p class="contributor-card-bio">Editor-in-chief of Mere Orthodoxy and author of <em>In Search of the Common Good</em> and <em>What Are Christians For?</em>. His writing has appeared in The Atlantic, Commonweal, First Things, Christianity Today, and elsewhere.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="contributor-card contributor-card--static">
          <div class="contributor-card-portrait" aria-hidden="true">
            {{#get "tags" filter="slug:author-mark-kremer" limit="1"}}
              {{#foreach tags}}{{#if feature_image}}<img src="{{img_url feature_image size="s"}}" alt="Mark Kremer" />{{else}}<span class="contributor-card-initial">Mark Kremer</span>{{/if}}{{/foreach}}
            {{else}}<span class="contributor-card-initial">Mark Kremer</span>{{/get}}
          </div>
          <div class="contributor-card-body">
            <h3 class="contributor-card-name"><em>Mark Kremer</em></h3>
            <p class="contributor-card-role">Publisher &amp; Executive Director</p>
            <p class="contributor-card-bio">Thirty years of pastoral leadership and over twenty years in non-profit leadership and publishing. Consults with churches and ministries on leadership, vision, strategic planning, and stewardship.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="contributor-card contributor-card--static">
          <div class="contributor-card-portrait" aria-hidden="true">
            {{#get "tags" filter="slug:author-ian-harber" limit="1"}}
              {{#foreach tags}}{{#if feature_image}}<img src="{{img_url feature_image size="s"}}" alt="Ian Harber" />{{else}}<span class="contributor-card-initial">Ian Harber</span>{{/if}}{{/foreach}}
            {{else}}<span class="contributor-card-initial">Ian Harber</span>{{/get}}
          </div>
          <div class="contributor-card-body">
            <h3 class="contributor-card-name"><em>Ian Harber</em></h3>
            <p class="contributor-card-role">Director of Communications &amp; Marketing</p>
            <p class="contributor-card-bio">Ten-plus years in marketing and communications with nonprofits, churches, Christian podcasts, and publications. Author of <em>Walking Through Deconstruction: How To Be A Companion In A Crisis of Faith</em> (IVP, 2025).</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="about-board">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-intro">
        <p class="eyebrow">Editorial Board</p>
        <h2 class="section-heading"><em>The editorial board.</em></h2>
      </div>

      {{!-- Board member photos pulled from Ghost author tags same
           way as Team above. Name, role, and bio are hardcoded so
           About-page-specific copy isn't coupled to tag metadata. --}}
      <div class="contributors-grid">
        <div class="contributor-card contributor-card--static">
          <div class="contributor-card-portrait" aria-hidden="true">
            {{#get "tags" filter="slug:author-jake-meador" limit="1"}}
              {{#foreach tags}}{{#if feature_image}}<img src="{{img_url feature_image size="s"}}" alt="Jake Meador" />{{else}}<span class="contributor-card-initial">Jake Meador</span>{{/if}}{{/foreach}}
            {{else}}<span class="contributor-card-initial">Jake Meador</span>{{/get}}
          </div>
          <div class="contributor-card-body">
            <h3 class="contributor-card-name"><em>Jake Meador</em></h3>
            <p class="contributor-card-role">Chairman</p>
            <p class="contributor-card-bio">Editor-in-chief of Mere Orthodoxy. Writes on theology, Reformed catholicity, and the formation of the local church.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="contributor-card contributor-card--static">
          <div class="contributor-card-portrait" aria-hidden="true">
            {{#get "tags" filter="slug:author-nadya-williams" limit="1"}}
              {{#foreach tags}}{{#if feature_image}}<img src="{{img_url feature_image size="s"}}" alt="Nadya Williams" />{{else}}<span class="contributor-card-initial">Nadya Williams</span>{{/if}}{{/foreach}}
            {{else}}<span class="contributor-card-initial">Nadya Williams</span>{{/get}}
          </div>
          <div class="contributor-card-body">
            <h3 class="contributor-card-name"><em>Nadya Williams</em></h3>
            <p class="contributor-card-role">Books Editor</p>
            <p class="contributor-card-bio">Classicist with a PhD from Princeton. Author of <em>Cultural Christians in the Early Church</em> and host of the Christians Reading Classics podcast.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="contributor-card contributor-card--static">
          <div class="contributor-card-portrait" aria-hidden="true">
            {{#get "tags" filter="slug:author-samuel-james" limit="1"}}
              {{#foreach tags}}{{#if feature_image}}<img src="{{img_url feature_image size="s"}}" alt="Samuel James" />{{else}}<span class="contributor-card-initial">Samuel James</span>{{/if}}{{/foreach}}
            {{else}}<span class="contributor-card-initial">Samuel James</span>{{/get}}
          </div>
          <div class="contributor-card-body">
            <h3 class="contributor-card-name"><em>Samuel James</em></h3>
            <p class="contributor-card-role">Author &amp; Director of Content Development, Crossway</p>
            <p class="contributor-card-bio">Writes and edits at the intersection of evangelical theology and digital culture.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="contributor-card contributor-card--static">
          <div class="contributor-card-portrait" aria-hidden="true">
            {{#get "tags" filter="slug:author-kirsten-sanders" limit="1"}}
              {{#foreach tags}}{{#if feature_image}}<img src="{{img_url feature_image size="s"}}" alt="Kirsten Sanders" />{{else}}<span class="contributor-card-initial">Kirsten Sanders</span>{{/if}}{{/foreach}}
            {{else}}<span class="contributor-card-initial">Kirsten Sanders</span>{{/get}}
          </div>
          <div class="contributor-card-body">
            <h3 class="contributor-card-name"><em>Kirsten Sanders</em></h3>
            <p class="contributor-card-role">Theologian &amp; Writer</p>
            <p class="contributor-card-bio">PhD in theology from Emory University. Writes on systematic theology, the life of the mind, and the vocation of the theologian.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="contributor-card contributor-card--static">
          <div class="contributor-card-portrait" aria-hidden="true">
            {{#get "tags" filter="slug:author-matthew-loftus" limit="1"}}
              {{#foreach tags}}{{#if feature_image}}<img src="{{img_url feature_image size="s"}}" alt="Matthew Loftus" />{{else}}<span class="contributor-card-initial">Matthew Loftus</span>{{/if}}{{/foreach}}
            {{else}}<span class="contributor-card-initial">Matthew Loftus</span>{{/get}}
          </div>
          <div class="contributor-card-body">
            <h3 class="contributor-card-name"><em>Matthew Loftus</em></h3>
            <p class="contributor-card-role">Physician &amp; Medical Missionary</p>
            <p class="contributor-card-bio">Serves as a medical missionary in East Africa. Regular contributor on evangelical culture, medicine, and Christian formation.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="contributor-card contributor-card--static">
          <div class="contributor-card-portrait" aria-hidden="true">
            {{#get "tags" filter="slug:author-susannah-black-roberts" limit="1"}}
              {{#foreach tags}}{{#if feature_image}}<img src="{{img_url feature_image size="s"}}" alt="Susannah Black Roberts" />{{else}}<span class="contributor-card-initial">Susannah Black Roberts</span>{{/if}}{{/foreach}}
            {{else}}<span class="contributor-card-initial">Susannah Black Roberts</span>{{/get}}
          </div>
          <div class="contributor-card-body">
            <h3 class="contributor-card-name"><em>Susannah Black Roberts</em></h3>
            <p class="contributor-card-role">Senior Editor, Plough</p>
            <p class="contributor-card-bio">Writer and editor focused on political theology, communalism, and the Christian imagination.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="contributor-card contributor-card--static">
          <div class="contributor-card-portrait" aria-hidden="true">
            {{#get "tags" filter="slug:author-tessa-carman" limit="1"}}
              {{#foreach tags}}{{#if feature_image}}<img src="{{img_url feature_image size="s"}}" alt="Tessa Carman" />{{else}}<span class="contributor-card-initial">Tessa Carman</span>{{/if}}{{/foreach}}
            {{else}}<span class="contributor-card-initial">Tessa Carman</span>{{/get}}
          </div>
          <div class="contributor-card-body">
            <h3 class="contributor-card-name"><em>Tessa Carman</em></h3>
            <p class="contributor-card-role">Literature Teacher, Editor, &amp; Writer</p>
            <p class="contributor-card-bio">Writes on literature, beauty, and the formation of the Christian imagination through reading.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {{> "membership-cta"}}

</main>
